# Public site URL (no trailing slash). Used for return/cancel redirects.
# For production, set this to your canonical domain.
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://sealinkapp.com

# Native app (Capacitor, Android only): optional override for the URL the WebView loads.
# If unset, capacitor.config.ts falls back to NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL.
# Local device testing (same Wi‑Fi as your PC): CAPACITOR_SERVER_URL=http://192.168.x.x:3000
# Android emulator reaching host Next dev server: CAPACITOR_SERVER_URL=http://10.0.2.2:3000
# After changing env, run: npm run cap:sync (embeds server.url into android/app/src/main/assets/capacitor.config.json).
# Production Android install: NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=https://your-live-domain (no trailing slash), npm run cap:sync,
# then Android Studio → Build → Generate Signed App Bundle / APK and distribute (Play Internal testing, etc.).
# CAPACITOR_SERVER_URL=

# Outbound email (password reset). Required on production or users will never receive mail.
# Gmail: use an App Password (Google Account → Security → 2-Step Verification → App passwords), not your normal password.
# Typical Gmail:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_SECURE=false
# SMTP_USER=you@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASS=xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx
# SMTP_FROM="SeaLink <you@gmail.com>"
#
# SMTP_FROM should be an address your provider allows to send as (often the same as SMTP_USER).
# Optional override if your host needs explicit TLS mode: SMTP_SECURE=true (465) or SMTP_SECURE=false (587).

# Optional: share session cookies between apex and www (HostOnly cookies are lost when switching host).
# MUST be bare hostname only: sealinkapp.com — NOT https://, NOT a path. Wrong values make browsers reject cookies
# so sign-in always fails. Prefer apex (not www-only) so both www and naked domain receive the cookie.
# Leave UNSET for local dev (localhost or http://192.168.x.x:3000). Setting a production domain while browsing
# by IP/localhost causes the browser to drop session cookies — laptop may “work” only if paths differ.
# COOKIE_DOMAIN=sealinkapp.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Live production app (Vercel / your host): payments + redirects
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL must be your real HTTPS origin (no trailing slash), e.g. https://sealinkapp.com
# Optional apex cookie: COOKIE_DOMAIN=sealinkapp.com (see note above; leave unset on localhost)
#
# Stripe (Dashboard → Live mode). Webhook: https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/stripe/webhook
# Events: checkout.session.completed, customer.subscription.updated, customer.subscription.deleted
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_...
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
# STRIPE_PRICE_MONTHLY=price_...
# STRIPE_PRICE_ANNUAL=price_...
# (Checkout is server-side only; no publishable key required in this app.)
#
# PayPal production: live REST credentials + billing plan IDs from developer.paypal.com (Live).
# PAYPAL_ENV=live
# PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=your_live_client_id
# PAYPAL_SECRET=your_live_secret
# PAYPAL_PLAN_MONTHLY=P-...
# PAYPAL_PLAN_ANNUAL=P-...
#
# Staging / local: use Stripe test keys (sk_test_…), PayPal sandbox (omit PAYPAL_ENV or PAYPAL_ENV=sandbox), and a
# separate Stripe webhook endpoint → its own STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET (whsec_…).
# Vessel listing one-offs use the same PayPal + Stripe server keys as above.

# Authorised voucher codes only you configure (JSON: CODE -> percent off 0–100).
# Example: 25% off with FRIEND25, or 100% off with COMP100.
VOUCHER_CODES={"DEMO25":25,"FULL100":100}

# Optional: OpenAI — 48-hour narrative outlook on the map page (server-side key only; never commit real keys).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# Optional: model for tide web search (Responses API + web_search_preview). Prefer gpt-4o if mini fails; defaults to OPENAI_MODEL or gpt-4o.
# OPENAI_TIDE_WEB_MODEL=gpt-4o
# Optional: custom base URL (Azure OpenAI, proxy, OpenRouter-compatible, etc.) — no trailing slash; /v1 added if missing is not applied; use full API root e.g. https://api.openai.com/v1
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# WorldTides (tide extremes / hi-lo tide table)
# Register: https://www.worldtides.info/register
# WORLD_TIDES_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# Optional: added to modelled “above mean” levels and to the “Est. abs” column for all tide tables (metres).
# Use when you want rough alignment to a local chart datum; default 0.
# TIDE_ESTIMATED_MSL_OFFSET_METERS=0

# Optional: Stormglass — global tide extremes (home “Sea state”) and /weather map wind + waves overlays
# (batched point API; rain/pressure on that page stay PacIOOS WMS). https://stormglass.io/
# STORMGLASS_API_KEY=your_key_here

# Meteostat via RapidAPI (nearest weather station observations)
# RapidAPI app: https://rapidapi.com/meteostat/api/meteostat/
# METEOSTAT_RAPIDAPI_KEY=your_key_here

# Optional: admin override email (this sign-in sees “Admin” on the home header and /admin/access for complimentary subscriptions)
# SEALINK_ADMIN_EMAIL=you@yourdomain.com

# Optional: only this sign-in may post area broadcasts visible everywhere (default matches admin email above).
# SEALINK_GLOBAL_BROADCAST_EMAIL=you@yourdomain.com

# Optional: /gear marketplace — listing lifetime and in-app reminder window (days).
# GEAR_LISTING_TTL_DAYS=60
# GEAR_REMINDER_DAYS_BEFORE=7

# Supabase (optional): when set, users, profiles, device limits, vessel/gear listings, listing images, and PayPal subscription rows use Postgres + Storage instead of local data/*.json and public/uploads.
# Create a project at https://supabase.com → SQL: run migrations in order through the latest in supabase/migrations (incl. marinas, map broadcasts, MOB 011_map_broadcasts_mob.sql, admin complimentary access 014_profiles_admin_granted_free_access.sql) → Storage: public bucket `site-uploads` (5MB max, image/jpeg, image/png, image/webp).
# Optional marina OSM import (after 005): npm run marinas:import:osm:dry   then   npm run marinas:import:osm
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co

# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_secret_from_supabase_dashboard
#
# Social sign-in (Google / Apple / Facebook): run supabase/migrations/020_user_accounts_oauth.sql on your project.
# Secret for signed OAuth state cookies (min 16 chars). Example: openssl rand -hex 32
# OAUTH_PKCE_SECRET=
# Google Cloud Console → APIs & Services → Credentials → OAuth 2.0 Client (Web application).
# Authorized redirect URI: https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/auth/oauth/google (add http://localhost:3000/... for local dev).
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Meta for Developers → Use cases → Facebook Login → Settings → Valid OAuth Redirect URIs:
#   https://YOUR_DOMAIN/api/auth/oauth/facebook
# FACEBOOK_CLIENT_ID=
# FACEBOOK_CLIENT_SECRET=
# Apple Developer → Identifiers → Services ID (Sign in with Apple enabled) + Keys (.p8). PEM may use \n in .env.
# APPLE_CLIENT_ID=
# APPLE_TEAM_ID=
# APPLE_KEY_ID=
# APPLE_PRIVATE_KEY=

# --- Area broadcast *reply threads* (Messages → Reply, /messaging/broadcast/[id]) ---
# Without Supabase, replies use data/broadcast-replies.json (lost on Vercel serverless restarts).
# With Supabase, apply migrations through at least:
#   017_broadcast_reply_threads.sql  (threads + messages)
#   019_broadcast_reply_seen.sql     (optional: Seen + reply alerts)
# Same NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY as above; no extra keys for this feature.

# --- Optional: Vercel KV (Upstash) — durable JSON when Supabase is off ---
# If both are unset, map broadcasts + reply threads fall back to local files (dev only on Vercel).
# Dashboard → Storage → KV → connect; names often KV_REST_API_URL + KV_REST_API_TOKEN.
# KV_REST_API_URL=https://...
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=...

#
# Import existing data/*.json once:
#   npm run migrate:supabase:dry
#   npm run migrate:supabase

# Optional: home map “nearby” sharing — radius (statute miles) and heartbeat stale window (seconds).
# MAP_NEARBY_RADIUS_MI=5
# MAP_PRESENCE_STALE_SEC=120

# Optional: area broadcasts — retention window (hours) and max posts per hour per browser session.
# MAP_BROADCAST_RETENTION_HOURS=24
# Man overboard alerts use a fixed 10 mi radius (see lib/map-broadcast-constants.ts); requires is_mob column (011 migration).

# Optional: marina bookings page — prefills "Open email" (safe to expose; use a shared inbox or role address).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MARINA_ENQUIRIES_EMAIL=bookings@yourdomain.com
